description.excerpt: FedX is a framework for transparent access to Linked Data sources through a federation

excerpt.body:
This is the major 6.0.0 release of FedX.

Main changes

* Support for using RDF4J workbench
* Support for using resolvable endpoints
* Improvements to optimizations (FILTERs, pushing LIMITS)
* Improved overall robustness and fault tolerance
* Improved query timeout handling
* Various bug fixes


See [changelog](https://github.com/VeritasOS/fedx/blob/master/changelog.md) for all changes

Note: this release is not fully backwards compatible to previous releases. See [upgrade notes](https://github.com/VeritasOS/fedx/wiki/Upgrade-Notes) for details.

FedX 6.0.0 is built against RDF4J 2.4.x, however, it should be compatible to RDF4J 2.5.x
excerpt.name: FedX 6.0.0

excerpt.body:
FedX 5.1.0 is a minor maintenance release, including the following changes
 * Built against RDF4J 2.3.2
 * Switch license to Apache License 2.0
 * Build using 3rd party dependencies from Maven central
 * Upgrade 3rd Party dependencies
 * Definition of pom.xml file
